<a href="http://news.bookweb.org/news/independent-bookstores-now-selling-google-ebooks%E2%84%A2" target="_blank">IndieCommerce Stores Now Selling <br>Google eBooksâ„¢</a>


        
    </div>
  
  
    <p><img hspace="5" height="104" width="125" vspace="5" border="0" align="right" alt="" src="/index/middleColumnParagraphs/01/content_files/file0/Google eBooks.gif" />On December 6, indie booksellers <a href="http://news.bookweb.org/news/indie-booksellers-google-ebooks-we%E2%80%99re-now-digital-game">truly became a part of the digital game</a> with the launch of <a href="http://news.bookweb.org/news/independent-bookstores-now-selling-google-ebooks%E2%84%A2">Google eBooks</a><a href="http://news.bookweb.org/news/independent-bookstores-now-selling-google-ebooks%E2%84%A2">&trade;</a><a href="http://news.bookweb.org/news/independent-bookstores-now-selling-google-ebooks%E2%84%A2"> on IndieCommerce websites</a>.<br /> <br /> An array of resources to help participating stores sell, market, and answer questions about e-books is now available on the new site, <a href="http://www.indiecommerce.com/">www.IndieCommerce.com</a><strong>.</strong> (An IndieCommerce user name and password is necessary to access the marketing materials.)<br /> <br /> There's also a wealth of info for ABA members interested in learning about IndieCommerce.</p> <p><strong>Learn more at <a href="http://www.IndieCommerce.com">IndieCommerce.com</a>.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>&nbsp;
  
  
